[2026-04-17T05:17:21.625Z] [INFO]             "text": "Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## Comprehensive Search Results: Claude Model Identifiers and Selection Logic\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **Model Definition and Mapping** (`/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1776402920632/src/models/index.mjs`)\n\nThis is the single source of truth for all model data and mapping. The file consolidates:\n- Model data structures\n- Validation and fuzzy matching\n- Model info and API integration\n- Support for [1m] suffix (1M token context)\n\n**Current Claude Models:**\n- `sonnet` → `claude-sonnet-4-6` (default, Issue #1329)\n- `opus` → `claude-opus-4-6` (Issue #1433)\n- `haiku` → `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` (Haiku 4.5)\n- `opusplan` → Special mode: Opus for planning, Sonnet for execution (Issue #1223)\n\n**Backward Compatibility Aliases:**\n- `opus-4-6` → `claude-opus-4-6`\n- `opus-4-5` → `claude-opus-4-5-20251101`\n- `sonnet-4-6` → `claude-sonnet-4-6` (Issue #1329)\n- `sonnet-4-5` → `claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929`\n- `haiku-4-5` → `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001`\n- Full IDs like `claude-sonnet-4-6` also work directly\n\n**Agent Models:**\n- Default: `nemotron-3-super-free` (Issue #1563 - free promotion ended April 2026)\n- Free models from OpenCode Zen and Kilo Gateway\n- Various aliases and provider prefixes (opencode/, kilo/)\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `mapModelForTool(tool, model)` - Maps model names to full IDs\n- `validateModelName(model, tool)` - Validates with fuzzy matching suggestions\n- `supports1mContext(model, tool)` - Checks 1M context support\n- `getValidModelsForTool(tool)` - Lists valid models for tool\n- `getAvailableModelNames(tool)` - Gets short names for CLI help\n- `resolveModelId(model, tool)` - Resolves aliases to full IDs\n- `buildModelInfoString()` - Formats model info for PR comments\n- `getModelInfoForComment()` - Fetches metadata from models.dev API\n\n### 2. **Tool Flag and Model Selection Logic**\n\n**In `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1776402920632/src/solve.config.lib.mjs`:**\n- Line 296-301: `--tool` option definition with choices: `['claude', 'opencode', 'codex', 'agent']`, default: `'claude'`\n- Line 476-484: `--model` option with dynamic default based on tool selection\n- Line 587-600: Post-processing for model defaults by tool\n- Issue #1473: Centralized model defaults in `/src/models/index.mjs`\n\n**Tool-specific Model Defaults:**\n```javascript\ndefaultModels = {\n  claude: 'sonnet',           // claude-sonnet-4-6\n  agent: 'nemotron-3-super-free',  // Issue #1563\n  opencode: 'grok-code-fast-1',\n  codex: 'gpt-5.4',\n}\n```\n\n**Model Selection Flow:**\n1. User provides `--tool` (default: 'claude')\n2. User provides `--model` (default: depends on tool)\n3. If not provided, system uses tool-specific default\n4. Model is validated against allowed models for that tool\n5. Full model ID is resolved from alias\n\n### 3. **How --tool claude Flag Works**\n\nLocated in `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1776402920632/src/solve.mjs`:\n- Line 90-96: Routes to Claude-specific execution path\n- Line 179-180: Sets tool and validates model\n- Line 814: Determines resume command format based on tool\n- Claude CLI is invoked with `claude --model <model-id>` command\n\nThe `--tool` flag determines:\n1. Which executable/API to call (claude, agent, opencode, or codex)\n2. Which model mappings apply\n3. Which tool-specific validation rules to use\n4. How to format result comments and model info\n\n### 4. **Configuration Files**\n\n**`.env.example`:**\n- Environment variables for model overrides\n- Example: `TELEGRAM_HIVE_OVERRIDES=\"(--model sonnet)\"`\n\n**`solve.config.lib.mjs`:**\n- Complete option definitions for all CLI flags\n- Dynamic default functions\n- Tool and model option specifications\n\n**Package.json:**\n- No model information stored; models are all in code\n\n### 5. **Test Files for Model Selection**\n\nComprehensive tests located in `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1776402920632/tests/`:\n\n**`model-info.test.mjs`:**\n- 60+ tests for model info display, tool names, model resolution\n- Tests for multi-model scenarios (main + supporting models)\n- Covers all tools: claude, agent, opencode, codex\n- Tests for models.dev API integration\n\n**`test-opus-46-model-support.mjs`:**\n- Tests for Opus 4.6 as default (Issue #1433)\n- [1m] suffix parsing and validation\n- Backward compatibility with Opus 4.5\n- Max output tokens per model\n- Thinking budget allocation per model\n\n**`test-sonnet-46-model-support.mjs`:**\n- Tests for Sonnet 4.6 as default (Issue #1329)\n- [1m] suffix support for Sonnet 4.6\n- Backward compatibility with Sonnet 4.5\n- Direct model ID support\n\n**`test-agent-model-validation.mjs`:**\n- Tests for agent-specific free models\n- OpenCode Zen vs Kilo Gateway models\n- Model mapping for agent tool\n\n**`test-opusplan-support.mjs`:**\n- Tests for opusplan mode (opus + sonnet dual model)\n\n**`test-free-models.mjs`:**\n- Tests for free model pricing and deprecation status\n\n**`test-synthetic-model-filter.mjs`:**\n- Tests for model filtering and validation\n\n### 6. **Related Documentation**\n\n**Case Studies:**\n- `/docs/case-studies/issue-1329/README.md` - Sonnet 4.6 migration\n- `/docs/case-studies/issue-1221/README.md` - Opus model support\n- `/docs/case-studies/issue-789-unrecognized-model-error/` - Model error handling\n\n**Key Issues Referenced:**\n- #1221: [1m] suffix and Opus 4.6 support\n- #1238: Opus 4.5/4.6 max output tokens\n- #1329: Sonnet 4.6 default model\n- #1433: Opus 4.6 as default for 'opus' alias\n- #1563: Agent default model change (nemotron-3-super-free)\n- #1473: Centralized model definitions\n\n### 7. **Model Name/Identifier Support Summary**\n\n**Currently Supported Claude Models:**\n- Full IDs: `claude-opus-4-6`, `claude-sonnet-4-6`, `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001`, etc.\n- Short aliases: `opus`, `sonnet`, `haiku`, `opusplan`\n- Version aliases: `opus-4-6`, `opus-4-5`, `sonnet-4-6`, `sonnet-4-5`, `haiku-4-5`\n- Full version aliases: `claude-opus-4-6`, `claude-sonnet-4-6`, etc.\n- [1m] suffix: All models support `[1m]` suffix for 1M context when compatible\n\n**Agent Model Examples:**\n- `grok`, `grok-code`, `grok-code-fast-1` → `opencode/grok-code`\n- `nemotron-3-super-free` → `opencode/nemotron-3-super-free`\n- `glm-5-free`, `deepseek-r1-free` → Kilo gateway models\n- Full provider syntax: `opencode/model-name`, `kilo/model-name`\n\n**Codex Models:**\n- `gpt-5`, `gpt-5.4`, `gpt-5.4-mini`, `gpt-5.3-codex`, `o3-mini`\n\nThis centralized system in `/src/models/index.mjs` ensures consistent model handling across all tools and provides extensive validation, fuzzy matching, and helpful error messages."
