[2026-04-17T05:17:51.051Z] [INFO]         "content": "# Claude Opus 4.7 Technical Details\n\n## Model Information\n- **Model ID**: `claude-opus-4-7`\n- **Release Date**: April 16, 2026\n- **Status**: Generally available across Claude products, API, Amazon Bedrock, Google Cloud Vertex AI, and Microsoft Foundry\n\n## Pricing\n- Input tokens: $5 per million\n- Output tokens: $25 per million\n- (Same as Opus 4.6)\n\n## Key Capabilities\n\n**Vision Enhancement**: Opus 4.7 accepts images up to 2,576 pixels on the long edge (~3.75 megapixels)—\"more than three times as many as prior Claude models.\"\n\n**Reasoning**: The model demonstrates \"notable improvement on Opus 4.6 in advanced software engineering\" and \"handles complex, long-running tasks with rigor and consistency.\"\n\n**Instruction Following**: Users should note that \"prompts written for earlier models can sometimes now produce unexpected results\" since this version interprets instructions more literally.\n\n## Notable Changes from Opus 4.6\n\n1. **Tokenizer Update**: Same input may consume 1.0–1.35× more tokens depending on content type\n2. **Output Tokens**: Model \"thinks more at higher effort levels,\" producing increased output tokens for improved reliability\n3. **Effort Levels**: New `xhigh` (\"extra high\") effort option added between `high` and `max`\n\n## Unavailable Details\nThe announcement does not specify context window size, maximum output tokens, or knowledge cutoff date."
