[2026-04-17T05:18:33.310Z] [INFO]         "content": "1\t# Case Study: Issue #1329 - Add Support for Claude Sonnet 4.6\n2\t\n3\t## Overview\n4\t\n5\tThis case study documents the implementation of Claude Sonnet 4.6 support in Hive Mind, including setting it as the default model for `--tool claude`.\n6\t\n7\t## Issue Details\n8\t\n9\t- **Issue**: [#1329](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1329)\n10\t- **Title**: Add support for Sonnet 4.6 and set it by default for `--tool claude`\n11\t- **Labels**: documentation, enhancement\n12\t- **Date**: February 2026\n13\t\n14\t## Model Information\n15\t\n16\t### Claude Sonnet 4.6 Specifications\n17\t\n18\t| Attribute                     | Value                                    |\n19\t| ----------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |\n20\t| **API Model ID**              | `claude-sonnet-4-6`                      |\n21\t| **Release Date**              | February 17, 2026                        |\n22\t| **Context Window**            | 200K tokens (default) / 1M tokens (beta) |\n23\t| **Max Output**                | 64K tokens                               |\n24\t| **Pricing**                   | $3 / input MTok, $15 / output MTok       |\n25\t| **Extended Thinking**         | Yes                                      |\n26\t| **Adaptive Thinking**         | Yes                                      |\n27\t| **Training Data Cutoff**      | January 2026                             |\n28\t| **Reliable Knowledge Cutoff** | August 2025                              |\n29\t\n30\t### Key Improvements Over Sonnet 4.5\n31\t\n32\tAccording to Anthropic's official release:\n33\t\n34\t1. **User Preference**: Users preferred Sonnet 4.6 over Sonnet 4.5 roughly 70% of the time in Claude Code testing\n35\t2. **Competitive Performance**: Users even preferred Sonnet 4.6 to Opus 4.5 59% of the time\n36\t3. **Computer Use**: Significant improvements in navigating complex spreadsheets and multi-step web forms\n37\t4. **Coding Performance**: Enhanced coding skills and instruction following\n38\t5. **Long-horizon Planning**: Better agent planning capabilities\n39\t\n40\t### Model Hierarchy (Current Generation)\n41\t\n42\t| Model             | Description                             | API ID                      |\n43\t| ----------------- | --------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |\n44\t| Claude Opus 4.6   | Most intelligent, for agents and coding | `claude-opus-4-6`           |\n45\t| Claude Sonnet 4.6 | Best speed/intelligence ratio           | `claude-sonnet-4-6`         |\n46\t| Claude Haiku 4.5  | Fastest, near-frontier intelligence     | `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` |\n47\t\n48\t## Implementation Plan\n49\t\n50\t### 1. Update Model Mappings\n51\t\n52\tAdd Sonnet 4.6 entries to:\n53\t\n54\t- `src/model-mapping.lib.mjs` - Main model mapping module\n55\t- `src/model-validation.lib.mjs` - Model validation with fuzzy matching\n56\t\n57\t### 2. Add Aliases\n58\t\n59\tSupport the following aliases:\n60\t\n61\t- `sonnet` → `claude-sonnet-4-6` (new default)\n62\t- `sonnet-4-6` → `claude-sonnet-4-6`\n63\t- `claude-sonnet-4-6` → `claude-sonnet-4-6`\n64\t- `sonnet-4-5` → `claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929` (backward compatibility)\n65\t- `claude-sonnet-4-5` → `claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929` (backward compatibility)\n66\t\n67\t### 3. Enable 1M Context Support\n68\t\n69\tAdd Sonnet 4.6 to `MODELS_SUPPORTING_1M_CONTEXT` to enable `[1m]` suffix support.\n70\t\n71\t### 4. Update Default Model Configuration\n72\t\n73\tChange `modelConfig.defaultModel` from `sonnet` (4.5) to `sonnet` (4.6) by updating the mapping.\n74\t\n75\t## Sources\n76\t\n77\t### Official Anthropic Documentation\n78\t\n79\t- [Claude Sonnet 4.6 Announcement](https://www.anthropic.com/news/claude-sonnet-4-6)\n80\t- [Claude Models Overview](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/about-claude/models/overview)"
