[2026-04-17T05:22:34.860Z] [INFO]         "content": "Testing Claude Opus 4.5/4.6 Model Support (Issue #1221, Issue #1238)\n\n\n=== 1. Opus Default Model Tests (Issue #1433, updated #1620) ===\n  opus alias maps to claude-opus-4-7 in CLAUDE_MODELS\n  opus alias maps to claude-opus-4-7 in availableModels (claude.lib.mjs)\n  opus alias maps to claude-opus-4-7 in claudeModels (models/index.mjs)\n  validateModelName accepts opus and maps to claude-opus-4-7\n  mapModelToId maps opus to claude-opus-4-7\n\n=== 2. Direct Model ID Tests ===\n  validateModelName accepts claude-opus-4-6 directly\n  mapModelToId passes through claude-opus-4-6 unchanged\n\n=== 3. Backward Compatibility Tests ===\n  claude-opus-4-5 alias maps to claude-opus-4-5-20251101\n  claude-opus-4-5-20251101 (full ID) still works\n  sonnet alias still works (now maps to Sonnet 4.6, Issue #1329)\n  haiku alias still works (regression test)\n\n=== 4. [1m] Suffix Parsing Tests ===\n  parseModelWith1mSuffix extracts base model and suffix for opus[1m]\n  parseModelWith1mSuffix extracts base model and suffix for claude-opus-4-6[1m]\n  parseModelWith1mSuffix handles case-insensitive suffix [1M]\n  parseModelWith1mSuffix returns no suffix for regular model\n\n=== 5. [1m] Suffix Validation Tests ===\n  supports1mContext returns true for opus\n  supports1mContext returns true for claude-opus-4-6\n  supports1mContext returns true for sonnet\n  supports1mContext returns false for haiku\n  supports1mContext returns false for non-claude tools\n\n=== 6. [1m] Suffix with validateModelName Tests ===\n  validateModelName accepts opus[1m] (now maps to Opus 4.7, Issue #1620)\n  validateModelName accepts claude-opus-4-6[1m]\n  validateModelName accepts sonnet[1m] (now maps to Sonnet 4.6, Issue #1329)\n  validateModelName rejects haiku[1m] (unsupported)\n\n=== 7. mapModelToId with [1m] Suffix Tests ===\n  mapModelToId handles opus[1m] (now maps to Opus 4.7, Issue #1620)\n  mapModelToId handles claude-opus-4-6[1m]\n  mapModelToId handles sonnet[1m] (now maps to Sonnet 4.6, Issue #1329)\n\n=== 8. Opus 4.5/4.6 Max Output Tokens Tests (Issue #1238) ===\n  isOpus46OrLater returns true for opus (now maps to Opus 4.7, Issue #1620)\n  isOpus46OrLater returns true for claude-opus-4-6\n  isOpus46OrLater returns false for claude-opus-4-5-20251101\n  isOpus46OrLater returns false for sonnet\n  getMaxOutputTokensForModel returns 128000 for opus (now Opus 4.7, Issue #1620)\n  getMaxOutputTokensForModel returns opus46 max for opus-4-6\n  getMaxOutputTokensForModel returns opus46 max for claude-opus-4-6\n  getMaxOutputTokensForModel returns default max for sonnet\n\n=== 9. Opus 4.5/4.6 Thinking Budget Tests (Issue #1238) ===\n  DEFAULT_MAX_THINKING_BUDGET_OPUS_46 is 31999 (aligned with standard models, Issue #1238)\n  getDefaultMaxThinkingBudgetForModel returns 31999 for opus (now Opus 4.7, Issue #1620)\n  getDefaultMaxThinkingBudgetForModel returns 31999 for opus-4-6 (aligned with standard, Issue #1238)\n  getDefaultMaxThinkingBudgetForModel returns 31999 for sonnet\n\n=== 10. Available Model Names Tests ===\n  getAvailableModelNames includes opus for claude tool\n  getAvailableModelNames includes sonnet for claude tool\n  getAvailableModelNames includes claude-opus-4-5 alias\n\n=== 10b. Shorter Alias Tests ===\n  opus-4-6 alias maps to claude-opus-4-6\n  opus-4-5 alias maps to claude-opus-4-5-20251101\n  sonnet-4-5 alias maps to claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\n  haiku-4-5 alias maps to claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\n  opus-4-6[1m] supports 1M context\n  sonnet-4-5[1m] supports 1M context\n  opus-4-5[1m] supports 1M context (Issue #1238)\n  mapModelToId handles opus-4-6\n  isOpus46OrLater returns true for opus-4-6\n  getMaxOutputTokensForModel returns opus46 max for opus-4-6\n\n=== 11. Case Insensitivity Tests (Issue #1238) ===\n  validateModelName handles OPUS (uppercase, now maps to Opus 4.7)\n  validateModelName handles OPUS[1M] (uppercase, now maps to Opus 4.7)\n\n==================================================\nTest Results: 54 passed, 0 failed\n==================================================\n\nAll tests passed!",
