[2026-04-17T05:27:19.238Z] [STDOUT] ## Summary

- Update `opus` alias to map to `claude-opus-4-7` (previously `claude-opus-4-6`)
- Add `opus-4-7` and `claude-opus-4-7` aliases with full validation support
- Add Opus 4.7 to `MODELS_SUPPORTING_1M_CONTEXT` for `[1m]` suffix support (1M context at standard API pricing)
- Keep `opus-4-6` and `claude-opus-4-6` as backward compatibility aliases
- Add case study documentation with model specs, breaking changes, and implementation details

## Breaking Changes in Opus 4.7 (API-level, documented in case study)

- Extended thinking budgets removed (must use adaptive thinking)
- Sampling parameters (`temperature`, `top_p`, `top_k`) removed
- Thinking content omitted by default
- New tokenizer may use 1.0-1.35x more tokens

